div1.p: IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT, FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF CHIN SHEUNG WING, FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.

Upon reading and filing the petition of Chin Sheung Wing made by his father, Chin Kim, duly signed and verified, whereby it appears that the applicant Chin Sheung Wing is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by Henry M. White, Immigration Comnissioner at the detention station in the City of Seattle, King County, Washington and said petition stating wherein the alleged illegality consisted, in which it appears that a writ of Habeaus Corpus ought to issue,

IT IS ORDERED that the writ of Habeaus Corpus out of and under the seal of this Court, directed to said Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration to have the body of the said Chin Sheung Wing before me in the Court room of this Court at Seattle on the 19th day of July, 1915 at 2 o'clock P. M. of that day, to do and receive order which shall then and there be considered concern- ing the said petitioner together with the time and cause of his detention.

IT IS FURTHER ORDERED that said Chin Sheung Wing either by answer or through his attorney immediately give over to the United States Commissioner in charge of the immigration service of Seattle, Washington such amount as may be demanded as a fund for the keeping of said Chin Sheung Wing until said action of this Court in hearing said petitioner or until such further action of the Government in relation to this case is concluded. Done in oven Court this 16 day of July, 1915.
IN THE District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Washington Western Division
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF CHIN SHEUNG WING, FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
SERVICE OF PAPERS IN THIS CASE MAY BE MADE ON DANIEL LANDON Attorney for Proctor for Petitioner.
